2026-04-21 01:29:17 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=["Control Module 6 internal wiring between Control Input Cable (+) 6 port 'n' and the switch/12 V line"] hypothesis_explanation="Measurements show ~12 V with correct polarity at the inputs and outputs of Modules 1–5, and 0 V at the output of Module 6 and at the load. Inside Control Module 6, the incoming positive pad (Control Input Cable (+) 6) has 11.99 V, while the internal 0 V, the outgoing + and − pads, and hence everything downstream are at 0 V. The switch itself has normal continuity, but one end of Control Input Cable (+) 6 (port 'n') that should connect to the switch/12 V rail is floating/disconnected. This localizes the voltage loss to an open connection between the positive input and the internal switch/12 V line in Control Module 6 (e.g., broken trace, loose solder, or mis‑seated connector). Repairing or replacing Control Module 6 to restore that connection should re‑establish 12 V to Modules 7–8 and the load, allowing the lamp to operate."
