description: With all modules connected as currently arranged and all switches ON, measure the voltage across the two cables at the output of Control Module 3 (the pair going from Control Module 3 toward Control Module 4). Check both cables relative to ground and the differential between them to see whether about 12 V with correct polarity is present after Control Module 3., outcome="At the output of Control Module 3, the positive cable ('Control Output Cable (+) 3') is at about +12.0 V relative to ground, and the negative cable ('Control Output Cable (−) 3') is at 0 V relative to ground. The differential between them is therefore about 12 V with correct polarity after Control Module 3, and there is a resistive path of 2.23 Ω between the two cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=150.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> cable connections and output of Control Module 4,
description: With all modules connected as currently arranged and all switches ON, measure the voltage on the two output cables of Control Module 4 (the pair going toward Control Module 5). Record each cable’s voltage relative to ground and the differential between them. Also measure the resistance between these two output cables (with power removed if required by the meter) to detect any low‑ohmic short like that observed at Module 3’s output., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 4 is at +11.9893 V relative to ground, and Control Output Cable (−) 4 is at 0.0 V relative to ground. Both cables show nominal continuity with measured resistance of 0.10 Ω each.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> cable connections and output of Control Module 5,
description: With all modules connected as currently arranged and all switches ON, measure the voltage on the two output cables of Control Module 5 (toward Control Module 6), each relative to ground and the differential between them. Then, with power removed if necessary, measure the resistance between these two output cables to check for any open circuit or unexpected high resistance. This will determine whether correct 12 V with proper polarity is being passed through Module 5 or lost between Modules 5 and 8., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 5 is at 11.99 V relative to ground, and Control Output Cable (−) 5 is at 0 V. Both Control Output Cable (+) 5 and Control Output Cable (−) 5 show nominal continuity with measured resistance of 0.10 Ω each.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> cable connections and output of Control Module 6,
description: With all modules connected as currently arranged and all switches ON, measure the voltages on the two output cables of Control Module 6 (toward Control Module 7), each relative to ground and the differential between them. Then, with power removed if required, measure the resistance between these two output cables to check for an open circuit or unexpected high resistance. This will determine whether correct 12 V with proper polarity is still present after Module 6 or is lost between Modules 6 and 8., outcome='Both Control Output Cable (+) 6 and Control Output Cable (−) 6 measure 0.0 V relative to ground, indicating no voltage present at Module 6 outputs.  \nContinuity tests show both cables have nominal resistance of 0.10 Ω, indicating intact conductors with no open circuit or unexpectedly high resistance.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 6 internal circuit,
description: With power applied and all switches ON, open the inspection panel of Control Module 6 and directly probe its internal 12 V line and 0 V line on both sides of the switch: (1) measure voltage between the incoming 12 V pad and 0 V pad (from Module 5), (2) measure between the outgoing 12 V pad and 0 V pad (to Module 7), and (3) verify the switch terminals continuity when ON. This will determine whether the loss of voltage occurs inside Module 6 (e.g., open switch, failed trace, or mis‑wiring) or at its external connections., outcome="Control Input Cable (+) 6 has 11.99 V present, while all other Control Module 6 cables (Input −, Output +, Output −) read 0 V. The internal switch in Control Module 6 shows nominal continuity when ON, but Control Input Cable (+) 6 has one end (port 'n') disconnected/floating that was originally connected to Control Switch 6.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
